ce, and I'm aiming for a clean implementation.\\n\\nI should pay attention to potential issues with whitespace, which might cause assertions to fail. Also, testing the attributes and ensuring namespace awareness seems crucial. I want to ensure everything works together as expected!\"},{\"type\":\"summary_text\",\"text\":\"**Exploring XML transformations**\\n\\nI'm considering how transformations preserve whitespace in XML, which affects the child element's exact value. If I'm using a namespace-aware approach, the output might include `xmlns=\\\"urn:test\\\"`.\\n\\nI think I should ensure there are no XXE flags and check for potential warnings from Checkstyle. There might be some dynamic lookups involved with `DocumentBuilderFactory`, which supports default namespaces. I’m curious about whether internal classes might not be available in Native; if so, `Class.forName` could return a null branch. Testing coverage likely relies on JVM with dynamic access, and that all sounds complex!\"}]}"}, {"type": "toolCall", "id": "call_UrK9YVP2mAcqBKe9g6rmH0IA|fc_0bf194598b56bb95016a0005282e6c81918a68a4d59abe7094", "name": "write", "arguments": {"path": "tests/src/org.wiremock/wiremock/3.13.1/src/test/java/org_wiremock/wiremock/XmlDomNodeTest.java", "content": "/*\n * Copyright and related rights waived via CC0\n *\n * You should have received a copy of the CC0 legalcode along with this\n * work. If not, see <http://creativecommons.org/publicdomain/zero/1.0/>.\n */\npackage org_wiremock.wiremock;\n\nimport com.github.tomakehurst.wiremock.common.xml.XmlDomNode;\nimport java.io.ByteArrayInputStream;\nimport java.nio.charset.StandardCharsets;\nimport javax.xml.parsers.DocumentBuilder;\nimport javax.xml.parsers.DocumentBuilderFactory;\nimport org.junit.jupiter.api.Test;\nimport org.w3c.dom.Document;\nimport org.w3c.dom.Element;\n\nimport static org.assertj.core.api.Assertions.assertThat;\n\npublic class XmlDomNodeTest {\n    @Test\n    void rendersElementNodeUsingDom2SaxTransformSourceWhenAvailable() throws Exception {\n        DocumentBuilderFactory documentBuilderFactory = DocumentBuilderFactory.newInstance();\n        documentBuilderFactory.setNamespaceAware(true);\n        DocumentBuilder documentBuilder = documentBuilderFactory.newDocumentBuilder();\n        Document document = documentBuilder.parse(new ByteArrayInputStream(\"\"\"\n                <root xmlns=\"urn:test\" id=\"123\">\n                    <child>value</child>\n                </root>\n                \"\"\".getBytes(StandardCharsets.UTF_8)));\n        Element root = document.getDocumentElement();\n\n        XmlDomNode node = new XmlDomNode(root);\n\n        String renderedXml = node.toString();\n\n        assertThat(renderedXml)\n                .contains(\"<root\")\n                .contains(\"id=\\\"123\\\"\")\n                .contains(\"<child>value</child>\");\n    }\n}\n"}}], "api": "openai-responses", "provider": "OCA", "model": "gpt-5.5", "usage": {"input": 378, "output": 943, "cacheRead": 16896, "cacheWrite": 0, "totalTokens": 18217, "cost": {"input": 0, "output": 0, "cacheRead": 0, "cacheWrite": 0, "total": 0}}, "stopReason": "toolUse", "timestamp": 1778386208012, "responseId": "resp_0bf194598b56bb95016a00052089f08191902ff2d0750f40dd"}}
